source_quote: Liquidity will be above old lows & highs, that’s where the 'Smart Money' will be targeting

signature.condition: IF price sweeps liquidity below equal lows during London killzone
signature.action: THEN look for displacement and FVG formation for long entry
signature.drawer_basis: ICT explicitly taught this as entry model pattern

source_quote: Run on the Buyside Liquidity (BSLQ) before expanding lower

signature.condition: IF price runs buy-side liquidity (BSLQ) before expanding lower
signature.action: THEN expect bearish continuation after liquidity sweep

source_quote: WHEN THE PRICE IS GOING SIDEWAYS (CONSOLIDATING) THE LIQUIDITY...WILL WANT TO SWEEP BOTH SIDES BEFORE PICKING A DIRECTION

signature.condition: IF price consolidates with liquidity building above and below
signature.action: THEN expect both sides to be swept before directional move

source_quote: if the 1H orderflow is bullish but there's a 5min consolidation...both sides will get swept, however, the overall direction will stay bullish

signature.condition: IF higher timeframe bias is bullish and lower timeframe is in consolidation
signature.action: THEN expect both liquidity sides to be swept but continuation in HTF direction

source_quote: price has to run the stops and quickly move away from that area

signature.condition: IF price aggressively moves away from a liquidity pool after sweep
signature.action: THEN confirm smart money involvement and expect continuation

source_quote: If the Market is in the Premium – we expect a Sell Program to occur

signature.condition: IF market is in premium side of dealing range
signature.action: THEN expect sell program and look for opposing PDAs to cover

source_quote: Price been forming small Higher lows, equal lows...the liquidity is building below it

signature.condition: IF price forms small higher highs/lows near consolidation
signature.action: THEN expect liquidity to be building below (retail stops)

source_quote: when price runs Liquidity before retracing – usually it will pull back deeper + the retracement will take longer

signature.condition: IF price runs liquidity before retracing

source_quote: price completely breakout above the main (highest) premium level – that's where price enters the External Liquidity area

signature.condition: IF price breaks above highest premium level into external liquidity
signature.action: THEN consider this as new expansion area

source_quote: when the momentum is low and price is either forming double, triple bottoms...it's like the markets are laying cheese below it

signature.condition: IF price shows low momentum forming multiple small highs/lows
signature.action: THEN expect liquidity to be building below (retail stops)

source_quote: Price broke out of the dealing range, at this point your longs from the Discount area should be completely closed or with a small portion running.

signature.condition: IF price breaks out of the dealing range
signature.action: THEN close longs from the Discount area completely or with a small portion running
signature.drawer_basis: Direct instruction on trade management after breakout

source_quote: WHEN WE HAVE A CLEAR ORDER FLOW AND A HIGHER TF DRAW ON LIQUIDITY (TARGET) - We enter on the INTERNAL LIQUIDITY & TARGET THE EXTERNAL Liquidity.

signature.condition: IF there is a clear order flow and a higher timeframe draw on liquidity (target)
signature.action: THEN enter on the internal liquidity and target the external liquidity

source_quote: When the price is making higher highs & higher lows... the informed money will want to attack. Uninformed money provides liquidity for the market makers.

signature.condition: IF price is making higher highs & higher lows with a visible trendline support
signature.action: THEN expect market makers to sweep liquidity below the trendline before reversal

source_quote: market created this huge imbalance by going down really fast... where's the biggest amount of liquidity resting? Right below the equal lows.

signature.condition: IF price creates a huge imbalance by moving down fast then fills it and rejects a bearish orderblock
signature.action: THEN look for liquidity below equal lows

source_quote: Price will always gravitate towards these levels... Price in most cases won't go more than 40 pips above/below the big figure without retracing back.

signature.condition: IF price approaches a big figure level (ending in 0/2/6/8)
signature.action: THEN expect price to gravitate toward it with max 40 pip extension before retracement
